= render 'breadcrumb'

.row.padded-row
  .col-md-12
    h1 GDS Vision and Goals for 2016/17
    p.lead This site explains what GDS is doing in the 2016/17 financial year.
.row.padded-row
  .col-md-12
    h2 Vision
    h3.vision Government is transformed by GDS supporting departments to deliver end to end services that are designed and built around user needs.
.row.padded-row
  .col-md-12
    h2 Goals that will help us achieve this vision:
    ol.nice_list
      li
        .point
          h3 Provide standards, policy, support, and guidance so that services and technology work effectively and consistently for the public and government.
      li
        .point
          h3 Create the platforms and tools that make it simple for government to build, iterate and retire services.
      li
        .point
          h3 Lead the digital, data and technology function so that government has the skills and capability it needs to transform itself.
      li
        .point
          h3 Build and leverage a diverse and inclusive workforce and workplace in GDS, and across the function, so that GDS and the technology function are seen as great examples within the sector.

.row.padded-row
  .col-sm-12
    h2 Goals by Business Group
    .noprint.expand_collapse
      = (params["expand_all"]) ? link_to("Collapse all", goals_path) : link_to("Expand all", "?expand_all=1")
.row.padded-row
  .col-sm-12
    / hide "new" button for now, the site is essentially read-only (data from google sheets)
      .span style="margin: 2rem 0"
        =link_to "Add New", new_goal_path,class: "btn-success btn-sm" if is_admin?
    - @group_info = {:Digital=>{:budget=>100,:headcount=>458},:Technology=>{:budget=>35.8, :headcount=>266},:Operations=>{:budget=>19.8, :headcount=>165}, :Data=>{:budget=>3.7, :headcount=>77}}
    /- Group.all.each do |group|
    - @group_info.keys.each do |group_name|
      - group =  Group.find_by_name(group_name.to_s)
      .well.group_well
        h2.heading-large =link_to group.name + " Group", group
        h4 Budget: Â£#{@group_info[group_name][:budget]}m
        h4 Headcount: #{@group_info[group_name][:headcount]}
      == render partial: 'shared/sub_goals', locals: {sub_goals: group.top_level_goals}

- if is_admin?
  = form_tag import_okrs_goals_path, multipart: true, class: "form-inline noprint" do
    .form-group
      =file_field_tag :file, :class=>"form-control"
    =submit_tag "Import", :class=>"btn btn-primary"
